    </section>

    <!-- Mission -->
    <section class="border-y px-6 py-16" style="border-color: var(--border); background: var(--surface-2);">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="mb-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--secondary);">Personal Mission</p>
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl" style="color: var(--text);">Equipping minds. Transforming lives. Advancing God's Kingdom through education, mentorship, leadership, and technology.</h2>
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-xl text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-muted);">
          <p>Visionary and multi-disciplinary Educator, Educational Consultant, Data Analyst, Web Developer, Curriculum Developer, Christian Mentor, and Counselor with extensive experience in educational leadership, institutional development, teacher capacity building, academic research, and digital innovation.</p>
          <p class="mt-4">Skilled in designing educational systems, developing curriculum frameworks, training educators, implementing technology solutions, and leading faith-based mentorship initiatives. Passionate about leveraging education, technology, and ministry to create sustainable impact within schools, communities, and organisations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About -->
    <section class="px-6 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--text);">The story behind Amakio</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-muted);">
          <p>
            I grew up in Uyo, Akwa Ibom State, where I attended primary and secondary school before earning my B.A.Ed. in English Education from the University of Uyo. From a young age, I was drawn to two things: teaching and building.
          </p>
          <p>
            For years I worked across classrooms and school offices — helping students learn, designing curricula, and watching administrators struggle with mountains of paper records. I saw schools lose exam results, double-pay teachers, and spend weeks compiling report cards by hand. I knew technology could solve this, so I taught myself to code.
          </p>
          <p>
            The real turning point was my son's birth. Holding Amakan — his name means <em>overcomer</em> — I found myself thinking about the future. What kind of education would his generation receive? I imagined a system where he could attend lessons and have everything in one place. Where I could follow his growth just by tapping my device. Where I could view reports and download them without calling to book appointments, without queues, without waiting.
          </p>
          <p>
            That vision became <strong style="color: var(--text);">Amakio</strong> — the overcomer's hub. A platform where the next generation can access their education without the obstacles my generation faced. Every feature I build, I build for Amakan. And for every child who deserves a school that works as hard as they do.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Core Expertise -->
    <section class="border-y px-6 py-20" style="border-color: var(--border); background: var(--surface-2);">
